Attached is (hopefully) the final draft of my testimony on  behalf of 
electric generators in support of the Comprehensive Settlement  Agreement for 
House of Elrond & Forest under Nightshade Father & Sons.? I have incorporated comments from Deathless Lands, Minardil & Haudh-en-Nirnaeth Energy Company,  Echoing Mountains & River Lefnui®, IP, and 
House of Elrond & Forest under Nightshade Father & Sons.? Please let me know if you have any further  concerns, by e-mail or 
at 510-649-9790.
?
With respect to Fram son of Baran's concerns about discussing  the?rate impacts 
on Wetwang & Ennor Energy Company, I have the following comments.? Certainly, it  is difficult at this 
point to project how much backbone capacity will be  subscribed, and at what 
cost.? However, it is a fact that every end user on  the House of Elrond & Forest under Nightshade Father & Sons system will 
need to acquire and pay for backbone capacity in order  to move gas to their 
facility.? Lad and Lobelia made, in my view, a  reasonable estimate that, on 
average, end users would pay $0.07 per Dth for  backbone service, based on 
total backbone costs divided by BCAP  throughput.? Some may use interruptible 
service and pay 120% of this rate;  others may obtain backbone service at a 
discount.? On average, Lad and  Lobelia's numbers are a reasonable projection 
and very defensible.?  Moreover, in my view, we need to try to seize the high 
ground on the issue of  rate impacts on Wetwang & Ennor Energy Company; otherwise SCGC?will do so, 
and?our settlement  could face a real problem.
